3330.name: Women participating in the three decisions (own health care, major household purchases, and visiting family) (% of women age 15-49)
3330.unit: own health care, major household purchases, and visiting family % of women age 15-49
3330.description: Women participating in the three decisions (own health care, major household purchases, and visiting family) is the percentage of currently married women aged 15-49 who say that they alone or jointly have the final say in all of the three decisions (own health care, large purchases and visits to family, relatives, and friends).
3330.s_name: World Bank – WDI: Women participating in the three decisions (own health care, major household purchases, and visiting family) (% of women age 15-49)

source.name: World Bank – WDI: Women participating in the three decisions (own health care, major household purchases, and visiting family) (% of women age 15-49)
source.additionalInfo: Statistical concept and methodology: Women participating in the three decisions (own health care, major household purchases, and visiting family) is the number of currently married women aged 15-49 who say they alone or jointly have the final say in the three decisions, expressed as percentage of currently married women age 15-49 who have been interviewed and It’s derived by dividing the number of currently married women aged 15-49 who responded they alone or jointly have the final say in the three decisions by total number of currently married women age 15-49 who have been interviewed.
